	- https://docs.spring.io/spring-framework/docs/current/reference/html/core.html#spring-core

Spring core - IOC(Inversion Of Control) with DI

outsourcing the work of object creation to the framework/spring core container
when an object is being created it might be dependent on other objects,
so dependency objects have to be created first and then injwcted in the objects that we request the container to create

configurations can done in 3 ways

XML based configuration
Annotation based configuration
Java Based configuration